fr.sorbonne_u.components.endpoints

Interface BCMCompositeEndPointI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AbstractEndPointI, CompositeEndPointI, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BCMCompositeEndPoint, CompositeURIServiceEndpoint

    public interface BCMCompositeEndPointI
extends CompositeEndPointI, java.io.Serializable
    The interface BCMCompositeEndPointI declares the methods that a BCM composite end point must offer.

    Description

    The redefinitions of the methods in this interface simply makes some typing constraints as well as pre- and postconditions and explanations more precise for BCM end points compared to generic end points.

    Invariants

     invariant       true        // no more invariant

    Created on : 2024-07-11

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
